OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F429A1708136528
OL,3,CHow virtual reality could help teens
OL,4,Cgrasp the dangers of carrying a knife
OL,6,F"You can see how easy it can be for
OL,7,Fteenagers to get on the wrong tracks
OL,8,Fif there's not the support and the
OL,9,Fopportunities for them and that's why
OL,10,Fwe need action."
OL,12,FYvette Cooper had the chance to try
OL,13,Fthe virtual reality experience while
OL,14,Fattending a meeting of the North East
OL,15,FKnife Crime Taskforce.
OL,17,FShe added: "Knife crime has become an
OL,18,Fepidemic and that is deeply damaging
OL,19,Ffor our young people and our
OL,20,Fcommunities.
