OL,3,CHow virtual reality could help teens
OL,4,Cgrasp the dangers of carrying a knife
OL,6,FChief executive Claire Downes said:
OL,7,F"VR is young people's tech. They see a
OL,8,Fheadset and it's interesting, it's
OL,9,Fsomething they understand and relate
OL,10,Fto. It's something they respect so I
OL,11,Fthink it's a way of engaging young
OL,12,Fpeople on a really genuine level.
OL,14,F"It's not a worksheet or a powerpoint
OL,15,Fpresentation - it's an interactive
OL,16,Freal world VR experience where the
OL,17,Fyoung people in it are recognisable to
OL,18,Fthe young people taking part. They
OL,19,Fengage with it and understand it and
OL,20,Frecognise those young people as their
OL,21,Fpeers."
